# /croq-tune — Kernel Tuning Dispatcher

When the user says "tune", "tuning", "optimize", "perf-tune", "auto-tune", "ai-tune", "sweep", or "/croq-tune":

1. Read `.claude/skills/croq-tune/SKILL.md` — the unified tuning protocol
2. Parse the user's `dsl`, `dtype`, and optional `shape_key` from their message
3. Read the matching `.claude/skills/croq-dsl-<dsl>/SKILL.md` for DSL-specific commands
4. Follow the protocol in `croq-tune/SKILL.md` exactly

These are the only two files needed per session. Do not load other `croq-*` skill files — they have been consolidated into `croq-tune/SKILL.md`.
